headline: Amphenol Blows Past Earnings Estimates. The Stock Sinks 12%.
summary: Amphenol  posted fourth-quarter earnings and sales that topped consensus views and issued a solid outlook for the current quarter.  Before the opening bell Wednesday,  Amphenol  reported adjusted earnings of 97 cents a share from sales of $6.4 billion, outstripping Wall Street’s forecasts.  Amphenol guided for adjusted earnings in the range of 91 cents to 93 cents a share.

headline: Amphenol (NYSE:APH) Reports Upbeat Q4 CY2025 But Stock Drops 13.3%
summary: Electrical connector manufacturer Amphenol (NYSE:APH) reported Q4 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 49.1% year on year to $6.44 billion. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($6.95 billion at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 3.5% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.97 per share was 3.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
